						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śāka 1504 (1582 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Records purchase of <hi rend="italic">tiruviḷaiyāṭṭam</hi> land from <hi rend="italic">Adhikāri</hi> Tiruvēṅgaḍamuḍaiyāṉ by Vēdavyāsabhaṭṭar Tiruvāḻi-Ayyaṅgār and seems to refer to the assignment of <hi rend="italic">vṛittis</hi> to persons to recite the <hi rend="italic">Tiruppāvai</hi> on specified occasions. The detail of date viz. <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1504, Chitrabhānu, Ṛishabha ba. 7, Monday, Aviṭṭam correspond to 1582 A.D. May 14, Monday, ·57; ·35.</hi></p>						

